[src:common-lisp/data-structures-p01] A *simple array* is neither displaced (using `:displaced-to`, to point to another array) nor adjustable (`:adjust-array`), nor does it have a fill pointer (`fill-pointer`, that moves when we add or remove elements).
[src:common-lisp/data-structures-p01] A **vector** is an array with rank 1 (of one dimension).
[src:common-lisp/data-structures-p01] A *simple vector* is a simple array that is also not specialized (it doesn’t use `:element-type` to set the types of the elements).
[src:common-lisp/data-structures-p01] `aref` *(array i j k …)* or `row-major-aref` *(array i)* equivalent to `(aref i i i …)`.
